OL,3,CMan who spent years in jail before
OL,4,Cconviction overturned loses
OL,5,Ccompensation bid
OL,7,FHis compensation bid was rejected on
OL,8,Fthe basis that it was not the case a
OL,9,F"new or newly discovered fact shows
OL,10,Fbeyond reasonable doubt that there has
OL,11,Fbeen a miscarriage of justice".
OL,13,FAfter losing his challenge in the UK
OL,14,Fcourts, including at the Supreme Court
OL,15,Fin 2019, he took his case to the
OL,16,FEuropean Court of Human Rights (ECHR)
OL,17,Fin Strasbourg, claiming the basis of
OL,18,Fthe compensation refusal violated his
OL,19,Fright to be presumed innocent until
OL,20,Fproved guilty.
