OL,7,FIn their decision dismissing the
OL,8,Fchallenge, the panel of judges at
OL,9,FStrasbourg ruled: "It could not be
OL,10,Fsaid that the refusal of compensation
OL,11,Fby the Justice Secretary imputed
OL,12,Fcriminal guilt to the applicant by
OL,13,Freflecting the opinion that he or she
OL,14,Fwas guilty to the criminal standard of
OL,15,Fcommitting the criminal offence,
OL,16,Fthereby suggesting that the criminal
OL,17,Fproceedings should have been
OL,18,Fdetermined differently.
